messageBody:
Hi,

Just joined this list after finding out about Shavian. I created a
phonetic alphabet for fun when I was younger that was organized in
much the same way as Shavian, except there were only 38 phonemes.
The characters were rendered on a 7 segment display (like a
calculator) for ease of displaying in electronic form. Glad to see
that Shavian has been proposed as a Unicode standard. Anyway, I'm
interested in becoming fluent in QuickScript, but am having trouble
downloading the file.

http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/Resources/QuikScript
Manual%28Image%29.pdf

It gets almost to the end of the download and completes suddenly,
leaving me with an unreadable file. Anyone have a way around this?
Thanks.

Jim Weaver
